# Code Review & Refactor Best Practices (meApp iOS)

## 1. Analyze Existing Code
- Review current implementation for architecture and patterns.
- Identify code smells or anti-patterns.
- Check for maintainability and readability.
- Verify separation of concerns.

## 2. Simplify and Optimize
- Refactor code to improve clarity.
- Reduce complexity and eliminate redundancy.
- Extract logic into helper functions.
- Prefer composition over inheritance.
- Ensure code is DRY and SOLID.

## 3. Strict iOS & SwiftUI Standards
- Follow latest iOS and SwiftUI best practices.
- Use dependency injection for all dependencies.
- No business logic in UI views.
- All strings must be externalized.
- Use the app's design system.
- Add SwiftDoc for all public elements.
- Ensure accessibility.
- Use previews for all views.
- Use proper state management.
- Use only one main view per file.

## 4. Build and Fix Until Clean
- Run full build after changes.
- Fix all errors and warnings immediately.
- Repeat build and fix process until clean.

---

**Summary:**
- All code must be reviewed, refactored, and maintained to the highest standards.
